The paper deals with the complexity of human computation in the context of cryptography and password generation, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a rigorous model of human computation and associated measures of complexity, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the analysis of algorithms and counting steps, which is related to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the human aspect of computation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
